Responding to U.N. Security Council trade and military sanctions, Iraq today rounded  up hundreds of foreign nationals in Kuwait.
(The Iraqi-installed Kuwait government had  earlier told foreign countries not to forget their citizens in Kuwait while punishing Iraq.)
Several hundred Britons, Americans, and West Germans were apprehended and some  were taken to Iraq.
World oil prices rose to their highest level in more than four years.
Iraqi troops moved toward the Saudi Arabian border on Thursday and Saudi troops  were reported moving toward the Kuwaiti frontier.
In Baghdad, Saddam Hussein  warned his nations's 17 million people to be on the alert for possible U.S. or Israeli  attacks. 
